    <note>Shan(1) Zhiwei [21477] According to Murong(1) Yanfeng's [10451] funerary inscription for father, Shan(1) Zhao [21476], Zhiwei was juren #1 in 1094 and then earned the jinshi as did all three of his younger brothers. But there are no Shan listed in the Zhejiang TZ jinshi list. Zhiwei received an early appointment in 1104 and may have earned the degree in the 1103 sitting, but without local history confirmation, I must assume that he failed the exam and also that his younger brothers were also juren, who later received civil service appointments. CBD, 4, 2964-5.</note>
